Kenya has asked the UN, on behalf of African states, to request an advisory opinion from the International Court of Justice on immunity for heads of state and government, and other senior state officials. In a report by the Associated Press on Wednesday, Kenyan Ambassador to the UN Lazarus Amayo asked secretary general Antonio Guterres to request the General Assembly to put the African request on the agenda of its upcoming session next month. This follows a decision by the African Union in January to seek an opinion from the court. Click here for the latest political news 